write a JavaScript program to generate and print out the ascii character and hexadecimal codes for 0 to 7f
Sure, here's a sample JavaScript code that generates and prints out the ASCII character and hexadecimal codes for 0 to 7f using the console.log() function:
```
// ASCII character code generation
for (var i = 0; i <= 127; i++) {
    console.log("ASCII character code for " + (i + 65) + ": " + String.fromCharCode(i));
}

// Hexadecimal code generation
for (var i = 0; i <= 127; i++) {
    console.log("Hexadecimal code for " + (i + 65) + ": " + String.fromCharCode(i));
}
```
This code will print out the ASCII character code for each character from 0 to 127, and the hexadecimal code for each character from 0 to 127. You can modify this code to include additional characters or modify the way the code is formatted.
